$GLW  

- Corning reports Q4 core EPS 72c, consensus 71c 

Reports Q4 revenue $4.41B, consensus $4.36B. Wendell Weeks, chairman, chief executive officer, and president, said, &quot;Since the launch of Springboard two years ago, we have transformed Corning&#39;s financial profile: From Q4-2023 to Q4-2025, we expanded core operating margin by 390 basis points to 20.2%, and expanded core ROIC 540 basis points to 14.2%, while nearly doubling adjusted free cash flow to $1.72 billion for full-year 2025. We now have a highly profitable launch point for future growth.&quot; 

- Corning sees Q1 core EPS 66c-70c, consensus 68c 

Sees Q1 revenue $4.2B-$4.3B, consensus $4.26B. Schlesinger continued, &quot;We enter 2026 with exciting momentum. In Q1, we expect year-over-year growth to accelerate, with core sales up approximately 15% to a range of $4.2 billion to $4.3 billion, and core EPS growing to a range of $0.66 to $0.70. We are also upgrading Springboard. Our internal and high-confidence plans now add $6.5 billion and $5.75 billion in incremental annualized sales by the end of 2026, respectively, up from our previous $6 billion and $4 billion.&quot; 

- Corning raises Springboard plan growth outlook 

Weeks continued, &quot;Excitingly, we have even stronger long-term growth ahead. Today, we are upgrading our original Springboard plan to now add $11 billion in incremental annualized sales by the end of 2028, up from our original $8-billion plan.&quot;

